Redman stabbed Mr Whiston inside the house before following him onto the street where he delivered the second, fatal wound.

Redman and Hennebry then fled the scene and boarded the bus on which the CCTV footage was filmed.

The court heard that Mr Whiston, from Clacton, Essex, collapsed onto the street outside the party and was rushed to hospital but was later declared dead.

